Sales and Marketing Activities
1- Purpose
This process defines the Marketing and Sales activities and the processes involved in selling
products to our customers, from finding a customer to winning an order.
2- Scope of application
 This procedure spans the interval from the receipt of the client’s request to the
completion of the job.
 All purchase orders, accepted tenders and contracts placed with the company, or any
amendments to same, will be formally reviewed prior to order entry / acceptance.
 Contract review will be co-ordinated as follows, to ensure that QMSrs has a complete
definition of the customer requirements and that any non-conformity has been
resolved:
Customer contracts - Sales Manager
Distribution Contracts - Sales Manager
Customer Order reviews - Sales Manager
Other contracts - Managing Director / delegated
 Controlled price lists and delivery schedules will be made available as required, to
provide quotations, contract review, and for answering general inquiries.
 Verbal orders are not accepted.
3- Responsibilities
 The Business Development team is responsible for long and medium-term business
planning and development, including designing solutions, estimating and delivering
proposals to Customers.
 Management Team.
 Sales Team.
 Order Processing Team.
